# Leading companies generate significant revenue from API-based platform businesses
@type: stat_callout

@stat: $180M | Addressable API Revenue | From 3 identified internal capabilities over 5 years
@stat: 73% | Gross Margin | Typical API/platform gross margin vs. 45% for services business
@stat: 340+ | Potential Developer Partners | In identified ecosystem segments willing to pay for access

@exhibit: Exhibit 1 — API Platform Revenue Opportunity
@source: BCG Platform Economics Study; API business model benchmarks from ProgrammableWeb, 2024

@notes: The 73% gross margin is the key CFO argument. API revenue is structurally high-margin — the infrastructure cost is largely fixed once built, making marginal revenue nearly pure profit.

