# API platform build requires a developer experience investment that most internal teams underestimate
@type: bullet_points
@layout: icon_rows

- @icon: rocket   | Developer portal with interactive docs, sandbox environment, and usage dashboard
- @icon: database | API gateway managing authentication, rate limiting, and usage metering
- @icon: shield   | Enterprise security: OAuth 2.0, mTLS, SOC2 Type II certification for external use
- @icon: chart    | Monetization infrastructure: usage billing, tiered pricing, invoicing integration
- @icon: brain    | Developer success program: onboarding guides, sample code, dedicated support tier

@notes: Developer experience is not a nice-to-have — it determines adoption speed. Stripe's success is 80% product quality and 20% developer documentation quality. Budget accordingly.

